g.text: PULL BASED MODEL WITH GITHUB ACTIONS

div.p: THIS MODEL SPLITS CI FROM CD FOR SECURITY AND SPEED.

SECURITY SCANNING MOVES TO REPO AND REGISTRY FOR CONTINUOUS SCANNING
(NOT ONLY WHEN CI PIPELINES RUN)
REGISTRY STORES AND SCANS IMAGES. PREVIOUS IMAGES PROVIDE ROLLBACK CAPABILITY.
CI NARROWLY FOCUSED ON BUILDING ARTIFACTS. DEVELOPERS MAINTAIN PIPELINES.
CD WORKS BY PULLING AND RUNNING IMAGES.
EXTERNAL SERVICES DO NOT HAVE PRODUCTION CREDENTIALS.
FOLLOWS GITOPS PRINCIPLES TO ENSURE SUPERIOR AUDITABILITY AND BCP.

g.text: PULL NEW CHANGES TO BUILD CONTAINER
TAG AND PUSH NEW IMAGE TO REGISTRY
POLLS REGISTRY FOR IMAGES ON CONFIGURABLE INTERVAL
SORTS AND COMMITS NEW IMAGE TAG BACK TO CONFIG
